RIYADH: The Islamic Development Bank has approved $176 million for food security, health, transport and water and sanitation projects in four member countries. The countries include Guinea Bissau, Togo, Benin and Cameroon, according to a statement.  #IsDBAMsNow President Dr. Al Jasser: Fighting poverty has always been at the core of our
partnerships & engagements with our Member Countries. We need novel, socially responsible solutions to fight poverty and promote shared prosperity.#BeyondRecovery #2022IsDBGroupAMs https://t.co/YM3xoSfobo pic.twitter.com/UZnjt53Egb — IsDB Group (@isdb_group) June 2, 2022 “Fighting poverty has always been at the core of our partnerships & engagements with our member countries. We need novel, socially responsible solutions to fight poverty and promote shared prosperity,” chairman Muhammed Al-Jasser said. This happens during the bank’s 346th session of its board of executive directors at Lamborghini International Congress Center in Sharm-El Sheikh in Egypt. 